# TitanOS earlyoom configuration.
# earlyoom watches free memory and, when it gets critically low, stops the
# single hungriest process BEFORE the kernel freezes the whole machine. On a
# 2 GB box this is what keeps the OS responsive when a game or build overruns.
#
#  -m 4  : act when available RAM drops below 4%
#  -s 4  : ...and available swap (zram) below 4%
#  -r 60 : report memory stats every 60s
#  --avoid : never kill the desktop/session core, so the OS itself survives
#  --prefer: prefer to kill the actual heavyweight (games/emulated Windows apps)
EARLYOOM_ARGS="-m 4 -s 4 -r 60 --avoid '^(openbox|lightdm|Xorg|systemd|tint2)$' --prefer '^(wine.*|steam.*|.*\.exe)$'"
